na...@gmail.com created issue #1
Jun 14, 2023 06:47PM
Component used: androidx.core.uwb
Version used: uwb:1.0.0-alpha05
Devices/Android versions reproduced on: Pixel 6 Pro Android 13 May 2023 updates for Play / Security

We are trying to initiate ranging to multiple Estimote UWB beacons using CONFIG_MULTICAST_DS_TWR, as the documentation states this has to be used for a list of UWB devices.
Estimote beacons require us to run as a Controlee.
There seems to be no UWB related tracing when looking at the logcat UWB tracing after doing the sessionFlow.collect.

So is multicast supported for Controlee and is it currently working?
We do see this issue which appears to have been fixed on 18th May 2023, so presumably this could be part of the July fix that was mentioned in our other issue...

As Android 14 Beta just stopped responding to the UWB initialisation call:
 clientSession = uwb.controleeSessionScope()

I had to turn off UWB and back on again in settings.

uci_backend_fira_ranging_start: session 1 cannot start due to aoa channel restriction

zi...@google.com <zi...@google.com> #16Jul 13, 2023 09:03AM

Hi,

I'm able to repro the issue on my side. As mentioned in comment#4, we have a known change in UWB stack: three fields (device address, dest address and static STS vendor ID) are reversed.

We've tested on two devices that when the controller side has the reversed bytes while the controlee side keep unchanged, the controlee will get statusCode = 37 error when ranging starts.

Please ask Estimote side to modify their firmware to fit this change.

    private suspend fun startRanging(devices: List<UwbDevice>, uwbChannelNum: Int, preamble: Int, sessionId: Int, sessionKey: ByteArray) {
        val uwbChannel = UwbComplexChannel(channel = uwbChannelNum, preambleIndex = preamble)

        var flowList: MutableList<Flow<RangingResult>> = mutableListOf()

        if (useMulticast) {
            devices.forEach {
                uwbDeviceAddresses += "${it.address} "
            }

                uwbConfigType = CONFIG_MULTICAST_DS_TWR,
                // SessionKeyInfo is used to encrypt the ranging session.
                sessionId = sessionId,
                sessionKeyInfo = sessionKey,
                complexChannel = uwbChannel,
                peerDevices = devices,
                updateRateType = RangingParameters.RANGING_UPDATE_RATE_AUTOMATIC
            )
            val sessionFlow = clientSession.prepareSession(rangingParameters)
            flowList.add(sessionFlow)
        } else {
            devices.forEach {
                uwbDeviceAddresses += "${it.address} "
                // Create the ranging parameters.

                    uwbConfigType = CONFIG_UNICAST_DS_TWR,

                )

            }

                updateRateType = RangingParameters.RANGING_UPDATE_RATE_AUTOMATIC
            )
            val sessionFlow = clientSession.prepareSession(rangingParameters)
            flowList.add(sessionFlow)
        } else {
            devices.forEach {
                uwbDeviceAddresses += "${it.address} "
                // Create the ranging parameters.
                val rangingParameters = RangingParameters(
                    uwbConfigType = CONFIG_UNICAST_DS_TWR,
                    // SessionKeyInfo is used to encrypt the ranging session.
                    sessionId = sessionId,
                    sessionKeyInfo = sessionKey,
                    complexChannel = uwbChannel,
                    peerDevices = listOf(it),
                    updateRateType = RangingParameters.RANGING_UPDATE_RATE_AUTOMATIC
                )
                val sessionFlow = clientSession.prepareSession(rangingParameters)
                flowList.add(sessionFlow)
            }
        }
        log(DEBUG,"Start ranging UWB channel $uwbChannelNum preamble $preamble devices: $uwbDeviceAddresses")

        // Start a coroutine scope that initiates ranging.
        job = scope.launch(uwbHandler) {
            try {
                flowList.forEach { sessionFlow ->
                    sessionFlow.collect {
                        when (it) {
                            is RangingResult.RangingResultPosition -> processRanging(it)
                            is RangingResult.RangingResultPeerDisconnected -> {
                                log(ERROR, "UWB Peer disconnected: $it")
                                diagnosticEventListener.onEvent(
                                    SamplingEvent.DiagnosticEvent.UwbRangingDisconnectedEvent(
                                        it.device.address.toString()
                                    )
                                )
                                cancelUwbRanging()
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
            } catch (ex: Exception) {
                log(ERROR, ex,"UWB ranging flow failed")
                diagnosticEventListener.onEvent(SamplingEvent.DiagnosticEvent.UwbRangingErrorEvent(ex.message ?: "UWB ranging flow failed"))
                cancelUwbRanging()
            }
        }
    }

Ok in trying to get multiple unicast sessions running I have found a few things...
It appears the the Peer disconnected is passing in the local UWB device rather than the actual device being ranged, which isn't exactly helpful, but I worked round it.
It also seems to need a separate UwbClientSession for each device and a separate sessionID.
I think a different sessionId is a problem with the current Estimote firmware, as they seem to be using a hard coded sessionId of 1, but I will check with them.
However I now can't seem to get any ranging results, even though it should work with one of the three devices...

We are now using AndroidX UWB Alpha6 and it has reduced the annoying redaction, so that's an improvement.

However we now see more disconnects and when ranging we seem to get a lot of other status messages with some ranging results.
So general ranging stability seems to be worse.

This is for a Pixel Fold and only attempting a unicast ranging session to a single beacon with rate set to automatic:
                        val rangingParameters = RangingParameters(
                            uwbConfigType = CONFIG_UNICAST_DS_TWR,
                            // SessionKeyInfo is used to encrypt the ranging session.

                            sessionKeyInfo = sessionKey,

                            subSessionId = 0,
                            subSessionKeyInfo = null
                        )
So we see RangingStatus set to 33, 34, 36, 37, 38 and some successful 0 results.
What do all these status results actually mean?

On the multicast front... as this issue was originally about multicast rather than all the unicast TWR issues ;)

Multicast to the latest Estimote firmware with Android 14 won't be possible as the beacons run as the controller.
However I did try creating separate prepareSessions for each beacon and I actually see ranging from the other beacon, but currently all the Estimote beacons seem to run with session ID set to 1, which means the prepareSession with that session Id gets the ranging result which is rejected as an unknown peer:
